Rando

Function: noun

Etymology: English (more accurately, American English, perfected in Washington, DC) 

1.  Abbreviation for random, typically denoting a person who is unknown, unexpected, unanticipated, or generally unbeknownst to the group he/she joins. 

''The jogging club anxiously awaited the arrival of a rando, Carol, who quickly became their star member and no longer warranted that label.''